## PCPC source rule
PCPC/wINCI is treated as a **licensed manual-import source only**.
- Supported import formats: CSV, TSV, XLS/XLSX, JSON.
- No scraping or bypassing authentication/paywalls is implemented.

## Canonical duplicate-handling and merge order
Deterministic matching order:
1. exact CAS
2. exact UNII
3. exact PubChem CID
4. exact ChEBI ID
5. exact normalized INCI name
6. exact normalized preferred/common name
7. exact synonym match
8. fuzzy candidates to review queue only

If same-name rows have conflicting strong identifiers, they are not auto-merged; they are added to conflict review.

## Canonical naming priority
1. PCPC INCI
2. CosIng INCI / glossary
3. existing canonical INCI-like name
4. UNII preferred name
5. PubChem preferred/IUPAC/common name
6. ChEBI preferred name

## Compatibility inference and curation
- Role tags inferred from source function text:
  - `ACTIVE`, `PRESERVATIVE`, `UV_FILTER`, `COLORANT`, `FRAGRANCE`, `SOLVENT`, `EMULSIFIER`, `SURFACTANT`, `HUMECTANT`, `EMOLLIENT`, `BUFFER`, `CHELATOR`
- Stability flags inferred from SMARTS rules (RDKit when available):
  - `OXIDATION_SENSITIVE`, `PHOTOLABILE`, `HYDROLYSIS_SENSITIVE` (plus mitigation defaults)
- Pairwise tags inferred from deterministic name/role/SMARTS heuristics:
  - `STRONG_ACID`, `CATIONIC`, `ANIONIC`, `OXIDIZER`, `REDUCER`, `PEPTIDE`, `METAL_REACTIVE`, `ESTER_RICH`, `POLYPHENOL`
- Curated compatibility import writes pH/stability/pairwise/manual overrides and evidence.
- pH/stability compatibility data is persisted locally and reused during formulation; it is not fetched live.

## Main tables
- Source raw/parsed:
  - `cosing_raw`, `cosing_parsed`
  - `fda_iid_raw`, `fda_iid_parsed`
  - `fda_unii_raw`, `fda_unii_parsed`
  - `pcpc_raw`, `pcpc_parsed`
  - `chebi_raw`, `chebi_parsed`
  - `pubchem_raw`, `ingredient_enrichment`
- Canonical layer:
  - `ingredient_master`
  - `ingredient_aliases`
  - `ingredient_identifiers`
  - `source_links`
  - `ingredient_merge_candidates`
  - `ingredient_merge_decisions`
  - `normalization_runs`

## CLI
```bash
# Phase-1 / existing
ingredient-pipeline acquire-cosing
ingredient-pipeline parse-cosing
ingredient-pipeline enrich-pubchem

# FDA
ingredient-pipeline acquire-fda-iid
ingredient-pipeline parse-fda-iid
ingredient-pipeline acquire-fda-unii
ingredient-pipeline parse-fda-unii

# PCPC manual import
ingredient-pipeline import-pcpc --file /path/to/pcpc_export.xlsx
ingredient-pipeline parse-pcpc

# ChEBI (optional; set CHEBI_ENABLED=true)
ingredient-pipeline acquire-chebi --max-queries 200
ingredient-pipeline parse-chebi

# Canonical rebuild
ingredient-pipeline rebuild-master-ingredients
# or
ingredient-pipeline normalize-identities

# End-to-end phase2
ingredient-pipeline phase2-run-all

# Exports
ingredient-pipeline export-master-jsonl --out-dir ./data/exports
ingredient-pipeline export-master-csv --out ./data/exports/master_summary.csv
ingredient-pipeline export-duplicates-report --out ./data/exports/duplicates_report.csv
ingredient-pipeline export-conflicts-report --out ./data/exports/conflicts_report.csv

# Compatibility layer commands
ingredient-pipeline infer-role-tags
ingredient-pipeline infer-stability
ingredient-pipeline infer-pairwise-tags
ingredient-pipeline create-curated-template
ingredient-pipeline import-curated-compatibility --file ./data/templates/compatibility_seed_template.csv
ingredient-pipeline score-priority-ingredients --version v1
ingredient-pipeline select-top-ingredients --top-n 300
ingredient-pipeline export-top-ingredients --out ./data/exports/top_ingredients.csv --top-n 300
ingredient-pipeline enrich-compatibility --top-n 300
```

Top-ingredient selection:
- score all ingredients with weighted deterministic factors
- select top `100` as `TIER_1`
- select next `200` (default up to `300`) as `TIER_2`
- configurable via `--top-n`

## Deferred
- Regulatory validation engine.
- Aggressive fuzzy auto-merge.
- Embeddings/vector/PDF semantic search.
- Final compatibility scoring engine (pairwise scoring logic is not implemented yet).
